Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Schizachyrium scoparium

Assembly is allelic, and the genome is tetraploid. It has a haploid genome size of 1700 Mb, and has 20 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Schizachyrium scoparium from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Dotplot of Schizachyrium scoparium vs.Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Schizachyrium scoparium along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Schizachyrium scoparium is a tetraploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 4 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Schizachyrium scoparium

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Schizachyrium scoparium along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Schizachyrium scoparium is a tetraploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 4 lines for each subgenome.
